race.comment: BEDTIME ANGEL (4) progressed nicely, beaten a long neck over 1107m at Geelong. She draws an inside gate today and will jump and run. The blinkers go on for the first time and she rates to go one better. IMMORTAL STAR (2) switched to the premier stable and resumed with a solid placing at Kyneton. She's raced at Group level and has plenty up her sleeve. Proven second up and gets in well with the 3kg claim. ELECTRIC STAR (5) won at Sale on debut and was immediately spelled. Resumed there beaten 2L heavily bet in better class. Ben Melham sticks aboard and the mare has plenty of scope for improvement. APPPLEBY (14) presents fresh and just missed twice at the mile before the break. May need one, but has jumped out well and has to be kept safe.
